name: mathd_algebra_209
informal_prefix: /-- Suppose that $h(x)=f^{-1}(x)$. If $h(2)=10$, $h(10)=1$ and $h(1)=2$, what is $f(f(10))$? Show that it is 1.-/
formal_statement:
import Mathlib
import Aesop

set_option maxHeartbeats 0

open BigOperators Real Nat Topology Rat

/-- Suppose that $h(x)=f^{-1}(x)$. If $h(2)=10$, $h(10)=1$ and $h(1)=2$, what is $f(f(10))$? Show that it is 1.-/
theorem mathd_algebra_209 (σ : Equiv ℝ ℝ) (h₀ : σ.2 2 = 10) (h₁ : σ.2 10 = 1) (h₂ : σ.2 1 = 2) :
    σ.1 (σ.1 10) = 1 := by
